Minister in the Presidency Jackson Mthembu met with President Cyril Ramaphosa at his Pretoria residence to discuss possible problems with the NDP. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Minister in the Presidency Jackson Mthembu says the National Development Plan will be reviewed. Mthembu met with President Cyril Ramaphosa at his Pretoria residence on Tuesday to discuss possible problems with the NDP. READ: Presidency: 'Ramaphosa committed no crime' The NPC discussed progress made since the implementation of the National Development Plan as well as challenges encountered. “The president has directed the NPC to review the NDP, so in the main, that was the discussion point,” Mthembu said. “From where we stand as the NPC, the NDP would have been reviewed by October this year and the product will then come back to the president.” Mthembu further stated that the NPC will speak to various stakeholders in order to deal with the omissions that are in the current NDP document.